#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.118"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.118:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.118:0.2"
msgid "12. Lokakāmaguṇavagga"
msgstr "12. The World and the Kinds of Sensual Stimulation"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 118. Sakkapañhasutta → sakka (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.118:0.3"
msgid "118. Sakkapañhasutta"
msgstr "118. The Question of Sakka"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.102"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.118:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

msgctxt "sn35.118:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sakko devānamindo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho sakko "
"devānamindo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"And then Sakka, lord of gods, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one "
"side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn35.118:1.3"
msgid ""
"“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme "
"no parinibbāyanti?"
msgstr ""
"“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t "
"fully extinguished in the present life?"

msgctxt "sn35.118:1.4"
msgid ""
"Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme "
"parinibbāyantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What is the cause, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully "
"extinguished in the present life?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.118:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Santi kho, devānaminda, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"“Lord of gods, there are sights known by the eye that are likable, "
"desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.118:2.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,"

# This is one of those passages where the “fuel” metaphor is tempting. We could say, “is supported and fueled … does not become extinguished.”
msgctxt "sn35.118:2.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ "
"hoti tadupādānaṃ."
msgstr "their consciousness relies on that and grasps it."

msgctxt "sn35.118:2.4"
msgid "Saupādāno, devānaminda, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati … pe …."
msgstr "A mendicant with grasping does not become extinguished."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.118:3.1"
msgid "Santi kho, devānaminda, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …"
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …"

msgctxt "sn35.118:3.2"
msgid ""
"santi kho, devānaminda, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.118:3.3"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,"

msgctxt "sn35.118:3.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ "
"hoti tadupādānaṃ."
msgstr "their consciousness relies on that and grasps it."

msgctxt "sn35.118:3.5"
msgid "Saupādāno, devānaminda, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati."
msgstr "A mendicant with grasping does not become extinguished."

msgctxt "sn35.118:3.6"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, devānaminda, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva "
"dhamme no parinibbāyanti."
msgstr ""
"That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully "
"extinguished in the present life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.118:4.1"
msgid ""
"Santi ca kho, devānaminda, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasant, sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.118:4.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them,"

msgctxt "sn35.118:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ "
"viññāṇaṃ hoti, na tadupādānaṃ."
msgstr "their consciousness doesn’t rely on that and grasp it."

msgctxt "sn35.118:4.4"
msgid "Anupādāno, devānaminda, bhikkhu parinibbāyati … pe …."
msgstr "A mendicant free of grasping becomes extinguished."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.118:5.1"
msgid "Santi kho, devānaminda, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …"
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …"

msgctxt "sn35.118:5.2"
msgid ""
"santi kho, devānaminda, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.118:5.3"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them,"

msgctxt "sn35.118:5.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ "
"viññāṇaṃ hoti na tadupādānaṃ."
msgstr "their consciousness doesn’t rely on that and grasp it."

msgctxt "sn35.118:5.5"
msgid "Anupādāno, devānaminda, bhikkhu parinibbāyati."
msgstr "A mendicant free of grasping becomes extinguished."

msgctxt "sn35.118:5.6"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, devānaminda, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva "
"dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings are fully "
"extinguished in the present life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.118:5.7"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
